weaving-crayon\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01Wk2GvJ5SMmh5XquxgZNBf5\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Here are **three approaches** for building the perf framework:\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Approach A: Dedicated `perf` package (Recommended)\\n\\nA new `cmd/entire/cli/perf/` package with a `Span` type that stores timing in context. Root spans emit a single structured log line on `End()` containing the full timing tree.\\n\\n**Pros:**\\n- Clean separation of concerns — perf logic doesn't clutter `logging/`\\n- Easy to evolve independently (add percentiles, histograms later)\\n- Testable in isolation\\n- Other packages import `perf` without pulling in logging internals\\n\\n**Cons:**\\n- New package to maintain\\n- Needs to integrate with `logging` for the actual slog output\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Approach B: Extend the existing `logging` package\\n\\nAdd span/timing primitives directly into `cmd/entire/cli/logging/`. The `LogDuration()` function already exists — extend it with span nesting.\\n\\n**Pros:**\\n- No new package — everything in one place\\n- Already has context helpers, slog integration\\n\\n**Cons:**\\n- Bloats the logging package with a different concern\\n- Harder to test timing logic independently\\n- `logging` currently has a focused, clean API — this would change its shape\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Approach C: Context-only timers, no framework\\n\\nJust pass a `map[string]time.Duration` through context. Each substep writes its duration to the map. The hook handler logs the map at the end.\\n\\n**Pros:**\\n- Minimal code, no new abstractions\\n- Uses only stdlib\\n\\n**Cons:**\\n- No automatic nesting — callers manually manage the map\\n- Error-prone (forgotten entries, key collisions)\\n- Hard to evolve toward richer metrics later\\n- Shared mutable state through context is a Go anti-pattern\\n\\n---\\n\\n**My recommendation: Approach A.** A dedicated `perf` package keeps the API clean, is independently testable, and gives you room to grow. The integration with `logging` is a one-liner — `perf` calls `logging.Debug()` on span end.\\n\\nDoes Approach A sound right, or would you prefer a different direction?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":235,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":48171,\"output_tokens\":501,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":235,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYh2eh5tsw6VqM2iApQGB\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"434aa3d5-1874-4c08-b13a-1b3b6cb2ffff\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T23:39:50.829Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"434aa3d5-1874-4c08-b13a-1b3b6cb2ffff\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation\",\"sessionId\":\"2d62938d-a5d3-4bac-9d0f-bf8056720e6d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"performance-logging-investigation\",\"slug\":\"wiggly-weaving-crayon\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"032128ee-920f-4524-8a71-0ed672cc437f\",\"toolUseID\":\"032128ee-920f-4524-8a71-0ed672cc437f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T23:39:50.848Z\",\"uuid\":\"1fde44ca-dee4-4f33-9780-a9153b775238\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"1fde44ca-dee4-4f33-9780-a9153b775238\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation\",\"sessionId\":\"2d62938d-a5d3-4bac-9d0f-bf8056720e6d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"performance-logging-investigation\",\"slug\":\"wiggly-weaving-crayon\",\"type\":\"system\",\"subtype\":\"stop_hook_summary\",\"hookCount\"