cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation\",\"sessionId\":\"2d62938d-a5d3-4bac-9d0f-bf8056720e6d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"performance-logging-investigation\",\"slug\":\"wiggly-weaving-crayon\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01WqRt5Y2mZYKDDDjvW3NJKk\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Let me present the design in sections. First, the core framework.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Section 1: `perf` Package — Core API\\n\\n**Package:** `cmd/entire/cli/perf/`\\n\\n**Types:**\\n\\n```go\\n// Span tracks timing for an operation and its substeps.\\ntype Span struct {\\n    name     string\\n    start    time.Time\\n    children []*Span\\n    duration time.Duration // set on End()\\n    attrs    []slog.Attr   // extra metadata\\n    parent   *Span         // nil for root spans\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**API:**\\n\\n```go\\n// Start begins a new span. If ctx already has a span, the new one is a child.\\nfunc Start(ctx context.Context, name string, attrs ...slog.Attr) (context.Context, *Span)\\n\\n// End completes the span. Root spans emit a single DEBUG log line.\\nfunc (s *Span) End()\\n```\\n\\n**Behavior:**\\n- `Start()` stores the span in context via a private key\\n- Child spans link to their parent automatically via context lookup\\n- `End()` on a root span calls `logging.Debug(ctx, \\\"perf\\\", ...attrs)` with the full timing tree\\n- `End()` on a child span just records its duration — no log emission\\n- Thread-safe is not needed — spans follow the single-goroutine execution path of hooks\\n\\n**Log output (single line from root span End):**\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"time\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n  \\\"level\\\": \\\"DEBUG\\\",\\n  \\\"msg\\\": \\\"perf\\\",\\n  \\\"component\\\": \\\"perf\\\",\\n  \\\"op\\\": \\\"postcommit\\\",\\n  \\\"duration_ms\\\": 342,\\n  \\\"steps\\\": {\\n    \\\"load_session_states\\\": 12,\\n    \\\"condense\\\": 210,\\n    \\\"carry_forward\\\": 89\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThe `steps` map is flat — child durations keyed by name. If nesting deeper than one level is needed later, we can switch to a nested structure, but flat is sufficient for the hook use case.\\n\\nDoes this core API look right so far?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":201,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":48912,\"output_tokens\":496,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":201,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYh2iXoQFjdhENzUxZmRD\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"93279170-cadc-4d53-91bb-742b52307f28\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T23:40:39.359Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"93279170-cadc-4d53-91bb-742b52307f28\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation\",\"sessionId\":\"2d62938d-a5d3-4bac-9d0f-bf8056720e6d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"performance-logging-investigation\",\"slug\":\"wiggly-weaving-crayon\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"4f551fa7-b626-408d-a7bc-7dacdf4ee86c\",\"toolUseID\":\"4f551fa7-b626-408d-a7bc-7dacdf4ee86c\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T23:40:39.378Z\",\"uuid\":\"5d6de9ed-3785-46f2-b075-af0a01765f75\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"5d6de9ed-3785-46f2-b075-af0a01765f75\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation\",\"sessionId\":\"2d62938d-a5d3-4bac-9d0f-bf8056720e6d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"performance-logging-investigation\",\"slug\":\"wiggly-weaving-crayon\",\"type\":\"system\",\"subtype\":\"stop_hook_summary\",\"hookCount\":1,\"hookInfos\":[{\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\",\"durationMs\":256}],\"hookErrors\":[],\"preventedContinuation\":false,\"stopReason\":\"\",\"hasOutput\":false,\"level\":\"suggestion\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T23:40:39.634Z\",\"uuid\":\"3324ed2e-f035-4f89-98cb-ae3120be302e\",\"toolUseID\":\"4f551fa7-b626-408d-a7bc-7dacdf4ee86c\"}\n{\"type\":\"file-history-snapshot\",\"messageId\":\"cd1be36b-ced6-498b-9e04-689fd7a7fd4d\",\"snapshot\":{\"messageId\":\"cd1be36b-ced6-498b-9e04-689fd7a7fd4d\",\"trackedFileBackups\":{},\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T23:43:35.504Z\"},\"isSnapshotUpdate\":false}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"3324ed2e-f035-4f89-98cb-ae3120be302e\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation\",\"sessionId\":\"2d62938d-a5d3-4bac-9d0f-bf8056720e6d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"performance-logging-investigation\",\"slug\":\"wiggly-weaving-crayon\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"The api looks right so far. For simple operations, it might be neat to have a method that takes a function like span.Measure(func() { doSomeWork() }) but generally speaking the low-level API looks right\"},\"uuid\":\"cd1be36b-ced6-498b-9e04-689fd7a7fd4d\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T23:43:35.194Z\",\"permissionMode\":\"default\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"cd1be36b-ced6-498b-9e04-689fd7a7fd4d\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation\",\"sessionId\":\"2d62938d-a5d3-4bac-9d0f-bf8056720e6d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"performance-logging-investigation\",\"slug\":\"wiggly-weaving-crayon\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01EUr7xVBiAUz5VYzSLdiCDy\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n\\nGood call — a `Measure` helper for wrapping simple operations without manual `Start`/`End`. That fits naturally as a method on `Span`:\\n\\n```go\\n// Measure times a function as a child substep.\\nfunc (s *Span) Measure(name string, fn func()) {\\n    ctx, child := Start(s.ctx, name)\\n    _ = ctx\\n    fn()\\n    child.End()\\n}\\n```\\n\\nOr as a package-level function for when you don't have a span reference:\\n\\n```go\\n// Measure times a function as a substep of the current span in ctx.\\nfunc Measure(ctx context.Context, name string, fn func()) {\\n    _, child := Start(ctx, name)\\n    fn()\\n    child.End()\\n}\\n```\\n\\nI'll include both forms in the design. Now for Section 2.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Section 2: Initial Hook Instrumentation\\n\\nFor the first iteration, we instrument these hooks — the ones that sit in the git commit path and directly impact user-perceived latency:\\n\\n**Git workflow hooks (block user commits):**\\n- **PrepareCommitMsg** — `getStagedFiles()`, session state loading, content overlap check, trailer writing\\n- **PostCommit** — session state loading, session data extraction, condensation, carry-forward\\n- **PrePush** — ref parsing, checkpoint branch push\\n\\n**Agent lifecycle hooks (block agent turns):**\\n- **TurnEnd (Stop)** — transcript validation, metadata extraction, file change detection, path normalization, `SaveStep()`\\n- **TurnStart (UserPromptSubmit)** — pre-prompt file state capture, session initialization\\n- **SessionStart** — concurrent session check, banner\\n\\nEach hook already has a single `LogDuration()` call at the top level in `hook_registry.go`. We replace that with a root `perf.Start()`/`span.End()`, and add child spans for the major substeps within each hook handler.\\n\\n**Example — PostCommit today vs. with perf:**\\n\\n```go\\n// Before: one timing for entire hook\\nstart := time.Now()\\n// ... all PostCommit work ...\\nlogging.LogDuration(ctx, slog.LevelDebug, \\\"hook completed\\\", start)\\n\\n// After: root span + substeps\\nctx, span := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"postcommit\\\")\\ndefer span.End()\\n\\n// substeps added inside strategy methods\\nctx, sub := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"load_sessions\\\")\\nstates := loadSessionStates(ctx)\\nsub.End()\\n\\nspan.Measure(\\\"condense\\\", func() {\\n    condenseSession(ctx, ...)\\n})\\n```\\n\\nDoes this instrumentation scope look right for the first pass?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":545,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":49113,\"output_tokens\":631,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":545,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYh2xMPinpDEQqzvUrNQ9\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"c122a9fc-4e35-46ad-8a35-5cc66846382a\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T23:43:50.710Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"c122a9fc-4e35-46ad-8a35-5cc66846382a\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation\",\"sessionId\":\"2d62938d-a5d3-4bac-9d0f-bf8056720e6d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"performance-logging-investigation\",\"slug\":\"wiggly-weaving-crayon\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"eef72500-7ffb-468f-99df-bf975ae51cf6\",\"toolUseID\":\"eef72500-7ffb-468f-99df-bf975ae51cf6\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T23:43:50.730Z\",\"uuid\":\"11bf1271-b4e2-4919-b31a-fb493bc6ef4b\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"11bf1271-b4e2-4919-b31a-fb493bc6ef4b\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation\",\"sessionId\":\"2d62938d-a5d3-4bac-9d0f-bf8056720e6d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"performance-logging-inve