kes `grep` filtering easy (`grep steps.condense_ms`).\\n\\nChild spans that aren't explicitly ended before the root ends get their duration calculated automatically (from start to root's end time) — no silent data loss.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Section 4: Package Structure\\n\\n```\\ncmd/entire/cli/perf/\\n├── span.go       # Span type, Start(), End(), Measure()\\n├── context.go    # Context key, span storage/retrieval\\n└── span_test.go  # Unit tests\\n```\\n\\n~300-400 lines total. No external dependencies — uses `log/slog`, `time`, `context`, and calls into `logging.Debug()`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Section 5: First-Pass Instrumentation Points\\n\\n| Hook | Substeps to measure |\\n|---|---|\\n| **PrepareCommitMsg** | `get_staged_files`, `load_sessions`, `content_overlap`, `write_trailer` |\\n| **PostCommit** | `load_sessions`, `extract_session`, `condense`, `carry_forward` |\\n| **PrePush** | `parse_refs`, `push_checkpoint_branch` |\\n| **TurnEnd (Stop)** | `validate_transcript`, `extract_metadata`, `detect_changes`, `normalize_paths`, `save_step` |\\n| **TurnStart** | `capture_file_state`, `init_session` |\\n| **SessionStart** | `check_concurrent`, `show_banner` |\\n\\nThe existing `LogDuration()` call in `hook_registry.go` gets replaced by a root span that wraps the entire hook execution.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Section 6: Privacy & Performance\\n\\n- **Privacy**: Spans only log operation names and durations — no file paths, prompts, or content. Consistent with existing logging guidelines.\\n- **Performance overhead**: Negligible. A few `time.Now()` calls and map writes per hook. The slog handler skips DEBUG entirely when log level is INFO or higher, so zero serialization cost in normal operation.\\n\\n---\\n\\nThat's the full design. Does this all look right before I write the doc?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":576,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":52368,\"output_tokens\":857,\"server_tool_use\":{\