ion\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"performance-logging-investigation\",\"slug\":\"wiggly-weaving-crayon\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01QPDsCy3k3ESVcuYxQarH51\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good, I have all the context. Now let me write the implementation plan.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":7809,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":71267,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":7809},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYhFQ1Gd7efQ24gpwP8uX\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"4e0ec709-5db1-4824-abf0-f68be934c0cb\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T02:26:48.714Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"4e0ec709-5db1-4824-abf0-f68be934c0cb\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation\",\"sessionId\":\"2d62938d-a5d3-4bac-9d0f-bf8056720e6d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"performance-logging-investigation\",\"slug\":\"wiggly-weaving-crayon\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01QPDsCy3k3ESVcuYxQarH51\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01NYxaBx4qxoBjafk8yCgQqH\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation/docs/plans/2026-03-03-perf-framework-plan.md\",\"content\":\"# Performance Measurement Framework Implementation Plan\\n\\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\\n\\n**Goal:** Add a reusable `perf` package with span-based timing that instruments all hooks impacting git workflow and agent lifecycle.\\n\\n**Architecture:** Context-propagated spans that nest automatically. Root spans emit a single DEBUG log line via the existing `logging` package. The `perf` package has no external dependencies — just stdlib + the `logging` package.\\n\\n**Tech Stack:** Go stdlib (`context`, `time`, `log/slog`), existing `cmd/entire/cli/logging` package.\\n\\n**Design Doc:** `docs/plans/2026-03-03-perf-framework-design.md`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Task 1: Create `perf` package — context.go\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- Create: `cmd/entire/cli/perf/context.go`\\n\\n**Step 1: Write context.go**\\n\\nThis file stores/retrieves spans from context. Follow the same pattern as `cmd/entire/cli/logging/context.go`.\\n\\n```go\\npackage perf\\n\\nimport \\\"context\\\"\\n\\ntype contextKey struct{}\\n\\n// spanFromContext retrieves the current span from context, or nil if none.\\nfunc spanFromContext(ctx context.Context) *Span {\\n\\tif v := ctx.Value(contextKey{}); v != nil {\\n\\t\\tif s, ok := v.(*Span); ok {\\n\\t\\t\\treturn s\\n\\t\\t}\\n\\t}\\n\\treturn nil\\n}\\n\\n// contextWithSpan returns a new context with the span stored.\\nfunc contextWithSpan(ctx context.Context, s *Span) context.Context {\\n\\treturn context.WithValue(ctx, contextKey{}, s)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Step 2: Commit**\\n\\n```bash\\ngit add cmd/entire/cli/perf/context.go\\ngit commit -m \\\"perf: add context propagation for spans\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Task 2: Create `perf` package — span.go\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- Create: `cmd/entire/cli/perf/span.go`\\n\\n**Step 1: Write span.go**\\n\\nThe core Span type with Start(), End(), and Measure(). Root spans log via `logging.Debug()` on End(). Child spans record duration only.\\n\\n```go\\npackage perf\\n\\nimport (\\n\\t\\\"context\\\"\\n\\t\\\"fmt\\\"\\n\\t\\\"log/slog\\\"\\n\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n\\n\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/logging\\\"\\n)\\n\\n// Span tracks timing for an operation and its substeps.\\ntype Span struct {\\n\\tname     string\\n\\tstart    time.Time\\n\\tparent   *Span\\n\\tchildren []*Span\\n\\tduration time.Duration\\n\\tattrs    []slog.Attr\\n\\tctx      context.Context\\n\\tended    bool\\n}\\n\\n// Start begins a new span. If ctx already has a span, the new one becomes a child.\\n// Returns the updated context and the span. Call span.End() when the operation completes.\\nfunc Start(ctx context.Context, name string, attrs ...slog.Attr) (context.Context, *Span) {\\n\\tparent := spanFromContext(ctx)\\n\\ts := &Span{\\n\\t\\tname:   name,\\n\\t\\tstart:  time.Now(),\\n\\t\\tparent: parent,\\n\\t\\tattrs:  attrs,\\n\\t\\tctx:    ctx,\\n\\t}\\n\\tif parent != nil {\\n\\t\\tparent.children = append(parent.children, s)\\n\\t}\\n\\treturn contextWithSpan(ctx, s), s\\n}\\n\\n// End completes the span. For root spans, emits a single DEBUG log line\\n// with the full timing tree. For child spans, records the duration only.\\n// Safe to call multiple times — subsequent calls are no-ops.\\nfunc (s *Span) End() {\\n\\tif s.ended {\\n\\t\\treturn\\n\\t}\\n\\ts.ended = true\\n\\ts.duration = time.Since(s.start)\\n\\n\\t// Only root spans emit log output\\n\\tif s.parent != nil {\\n\\t\\treturn\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\t// Build log attributes: op, duration_ms, then child step durations\\n\\tattrs := make([]any, 0, 3+len(s.children)+len(s.attrs))\\n\\tattrs = append(attrs, slog.String(\\\"component\\\", \\\"perf\\\"))\\n\\tattrs = append(attrs, slog.String(\\\"op\\\", s.name))\\n\\tattrs = append(attrs, slog.Int64(\\\"duration_ms\\\", s.duration.Milliseconds()))\\n\\n\\t// Add child step durations as flat keys\\n\\tfor _, child := range s.children {\\n\\t\\t// Auto-end children that weren't explicitly ended\\n\\t\\tif !child.ended {\\n\\t\\t\\tchild.ended = true\\n\\t\\t\\tchild.duration = time.Since(child.start)\\n\\t\\t}\\n\\t\\tkey := fmt.Sprintf(\\\"steps.%s_ms\\\", child.name)\\n\\t\\tattrs = append(attrs, slog.Int64(key, child.duration.Milliseconds()))\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\t// Add any extra attributes from Start()\\n\\tfor _, a := range s.attrs {\\n\\t\\tattrs = append(attrs, a)\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\tlogging.Debug(s.ctx, \\\"perf\\\", attrs...)\\n}\\n\\n// Measure times a function as a child substep of this span.\\nfunc (s *Span) Measure(name string, fn func()) {\\n\\t_, child := Start(s.ctx, name)\\n\\tfn()\\n\\tchild.End()\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Step 2: Run fmt and lint**\\n\\nRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint`\\n\\n**Step 3: Commit**\\n\\n```bash\\ngit add cmd/entire/cli/perf/span.go\\ngit commit -m \\\"perf: add Span type with Start/End/Measure API\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Task 3: Write unit tests for `perf` package\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- Create: `cmd/entire/cli/perf/span_test.go`\\n\\n**Step 1: Write span_test.go**\\n\\nTests verify: basic span timing, child nesting, Measure helper, double-End safety, auto-end of children, and log output format. The tests use a similar pattern to `cmd/entire/cli/logging/logger_test.go` — writing to a buffer via the logging package then parsing JSON.\\n\\n```go\\npackage perf\\n\\nimport (\\n\\t\\\"context\\\"\\n\\t\\\"testing\\\"\\n\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n)\\n\\nfunc TestStart_CreatesRootSpan(t *testing.T) {\\n\\tt.Parallel()\\n\\tctx := context.Background()\\n\\n\\tctx, span := Start(ctx, \\\"test_op\\\")\\n\\tif span == nil {\\n\\t\\tt.Fatal(\\\"Start() returned nil span\\\")\\n\\t}\\n\\tif span.name != \\\"test_op\\\" {\\n\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"span.name = %q, want %q\\\", span.name, \\\"test_op\\\")\\n\\t}\\n\\tif span.parent != nil {\\n\\t\\tt.Error(\\\"root span should have nil parent\\\")\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\t// Verify span is in context\\n\\tgot := spanFromContext(ctx)\\n\\tif got != span {\\n\\t\\tt.Error(\\\"spanFromContext should return the span set by Start\\\")\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\tspan.End()\\n}\\n\\nfunc TestStart_NestsChildSpan(t *testing.T) {\\n\\tt.Parallel()\\n\\tctx := context.Background()\\n\\n\\tctx, parent := Start(ctx, \\\"parent\\\")\\n\\t_, child := Start(ctx, \\\"child\\\")\\n\\n\\tif child.parent != parent {\\n\\t\\tt.Error(\\\"child span should reference parent\\\")\\n\\t}\\n\\tif len(parent.children) != 1 {\\n\\t\\tt.Fatalf(\\\"parent should have 1 child, got %d\\\", len(parent.children))\\n\\t}\\n\\tif parent.children[0] != child {\\n\\t\\tt.Error(\\\"parent.children[0] should be the child span\\\")\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\tchild.End()\\n\\tparent.End()\\n}\\n\\nfunc TestEnd_RecordsDuration(t *testing.T) {\\n\\tt.Parallel()\\n\\tctx := context.Background()\\n\\n\\t_, span := Start(ctx, \\\"timed_op\\\")\\n\\ttime.Sleep(10 * time.Millisecond)\\n\\tspan.End()\\n\\n\\tif span.duration < 10*time.Millisecond {\\n\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"span.duration = %v, want >= 10ms\\\", span.duration)\\n\\t}\\n}\\n\\nfunc TestEnd_Idempotent(t *testing.T) {\\n\\tt.Parallel()\\n\\tctx := context.Background()\\n\\n\\t_, span := Start(ctx, \\\"double_end\\\")\\n\\ttime.Sleep(10 * time.Millisecond)\\n\\tspan.End()\\n\\n\\tfirstDuration := span.duration\\n\\n\\t// Second End should be a no-op\\n\\ttime.Sleep(10 * time.Millisecond)\\n\\tspan.End()\\n\\n\\tif span.duration != firstDuration {\\n\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"second End() changed duration from %v to %v\\\", firstDuration, span.duration)\\n\\t}\\n}\\n\\nfunc TestEnd_AutoEndsChildren(t *testing.T) {\\n\\tt.Parallel()\\n\\tctx := context.Background()\\n\\n\\tctx, parent := Start(ctx, \\\"parent\\\")\\n\\t_, child := Start(ctx, \\\"child\\\")\\n\\n\\t// Don't explicitly end child\\n\\ttime.Sleep(10 * time.Millisecond)\\n\\tparent.End()\\n\\n\\tif !child.ended {\\n\\t\\tt.Error(\\\"child should be auto-ended when parent ends\\\")\\n\\t}\\n\\tif child.duration == 0 {\\n\\t\\tt.Error(\\\"child should have non-zero duration after auto-end\\\")\\n\\t}\\n}\\n\\nfunc TestMeasure_TimesFunction(t *testing.T) {\\n\\tt.Parallel()\\n\\tctx := context.Background()\\n\\n\\t_, span := Start(ctx, \\\"parent\\\")\\n\\n\\tspan.Measure(\\\"substep\\\", func() {\\n\\t\\ttime.Sleep(10 * time.Millisecond)\\n\\t})\\n\\n\\tspan.End()\\n\\n\\tif len(span.children) != 1 {\\n\\t\\tt.Fatalf(\\\"expected 1 child from Measure, got %d\\\", len(span.children))\\n\\t}\\n\\tchild := span.children[0]\\n\\tif child.name != \\\"substep\\\" {\\n\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"child.name = %q, want %q\\\", child.name, \\\"substep\\\")\\n\\t}\\n\\tif child.duration < 10*time.Millisecond {\\n\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"child.duration = %v, want >= 10ms\\\", child.duration)\\n\\t}\\n}\\n\\nfunc TestSpanFromContext_ReturnsNilWhenEmpty(t *testing.T) {\\n\\tt.Parallel()\\n\\tctx := context.Background()\\n\\n\\tif got := spanFromContext(ctx); got != nil {\\n\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"spanFromContext on empty context = %v, want nil\\\", got)\\n\\t}\\n}\\n\\nfunc TestStart_MultipleChildren(t *testing.T) {\\n\\tt.Parallel()\\n\\tctx := context.Background()\\n\\n\\tctx, parent := Start(ctx, \\\"parent\\\")\\n\\n\\tctx2, child1 := Start(ctx, \\\"child1\\\")\\n\\t_ = ctx2\\n\\tchild1.End()\\n\\n\\tctx3, child2 := Start(ctx, \\\"child2\\\")\\n\\t_ = ctx3\\n\\tchild2.End()\\n\\n\\tparent.End()\\n\\n\\tif len(parent.children) != 2 {\\n\\t\\tt.Fatalf(\\\"expected 2 children, got %d\\\", len(parent.children))\\n\\t}\\n\\tif parent.children[0].name != \\\"child1\\\" {\\n\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"first child name = %q, want %q\\\", parent.children[0].name, \\\"child1\\\")\\n\\t}\\n\\tif parent.children[1].name != \\\"child2\\\" {\\n\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"second child name = %q, want %q\\\", parent.children[1].name, \\\"child2\\\")\\n\\t}\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Step 2: Run the tests**\\n\\nRun: `mise run test -- -run TestStart -v ./cmd/entire/cli/perf/`\\nExpected: All tests PASS\\n\\n**Step 3: Run fmt, lint, and full test suite**\\n\\nRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n\\n**Step 4: Commit**\\n\\n```bash\\ngit add cmd/entire/cli/perf/span_test.go\\ngit commit -m \\\"perf: add unit tests for span API\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Task 4: Instrument hook_registry.go — replace LogDuration with root span\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/commands/hook_registry.go` — the `newAgentHookVerbCmdWithLogging()` function\\n\\n**Step 1: Replace LogDuration with perf.Start/End**\\n\\nIn `newAgentHookVerbCmdWithLogging()`, find the existing timing code (around lines 109-161):\\n\\n```go\\n// Current code (approximate):\\nstart := time.Now()\\n// ... hook logic ...\\nlogging.LogDuration(ctx, slog.LevelDebug, \\\"hook completed\\\", start,\\n    slog.String(\\\"hook\\\", hookName),\\n    slog.String(\\\"hook_type\\\", hookType),\\n    slog.Bool(\\\"success\\\", hookErr == nil))\\n```\\n\\nReplace with:\\n\\n```go\\nctx, span := perf.Start(ctx, hookName,\\n    slog.String(\\\"hook_type\\\", hookType))\\ndefer span.End()\\n// ... rest of hook logic (remove old start/LogDuration) ...\\n```\\n\\nThe `span.End()` in defer will emit the root-level perf log with any child spans added downstream by lifecycle handlers and strategy methods.\\n\\n**Important:** Add the import `\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/perf\\\"` and remove unused `\\\"time\\\"` import if no longer needed.\\n\\n**Step 2: Run fmt, lint, and tests**\\n\\nRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n\\n**Step 3: Commit**\\n\\n```bash\\ngit add cmd/entire/cli/commands/hook_registry.go\\ngit commit -m \\\"perf: replace LogDuration with root perf span in hook registry\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Task 5: Instrument lifecycle.go — TurnEnd substeps\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/commands/lifecycle.go` — `handleLifecycleTurnEnd()` (lines ~160-419)\\n\\n**Step 1: Add child spans for each major substep**\\n\\nThe TurnEnd handler has these sequential phases. Wrap each with `perf.Start`/`End`:\\n\\n1. **prepare_transcript** (~lines 184-189): `PrepareTranscript()` call\\n2. **copy_transcript** (~lines 201-219): Creating metadata dir + copying transcript file\\n3. **extract_metadata** (~lines 223-276): Extracting prompts, summary, modified files\\n4. **write_session_files** (~lines 278-294): Writing prompts/summary/context files\\n5. **detect_changes** (~lines 318-337): Git status + file change detection\\n6. **normalize_paths** (~lines 339-355): Filter and normalize file paths\\n7. **save_step** (~lines 360-404): Building StepContext + calling strategy.SaveStep()\\n\\nPattern for each substep:\\n\\n```go\\nctx, sub := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"prepare_transcript\\\")\\n// ... existing code for this substep ...\\nsub.End()\\n```\\n\\n**Important:** The `ctx` returned from `perf.Start` must be used for subsequent calls so child spans nest correctly under the hook registry's root span. Add import for `\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/perf\\\"`.\\n\\n**Step 2: Run fmt, lint, and tests**\\n\\nRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n\\n**Step 3: Commit**\\n\\n```bash\\ngit add cmd/entire/cli/commands/lifecycle.go\\ngit commit -m \\\"perf: instrument TurnEnd handler with substep spans\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Task 6: Instrument lifecycle.go — TurnStart and SessionStart\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/commands/lifecycle.go` — `handleLifecycleTurnStart()` (~lines 119-154) and `handleLifecycleSessionStart()` (~lines 61-117)\\n\\n**Step 1: Add substep spans to TurnStart**\\n\\n```go\\n// In handleLifecycleTurnStart:\\nctx, sub := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"capture_file_state\\\")\\n// ... CapturePrePromptState() ...\\nsub.End()\\n\\nctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"init_session\\\")\\n// ... EnsureSetup() + InitializeSession() ...\\nsub.End()\\n```\\n\\n**Step 2: Add substep spans to SessionStart**\\n\\n```go\\n// In handleLifecycleSessionStart:\\nctx, sub := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"check_concurrent\\\")\\n// ... concurrent session check logic ...\\nsub.End()\\n\\nctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"show_banner\\\")\\n// ... banner display ...\\nsub.End()\\n```\\n\\n**Step 3: Run fmt, lint, and tests**\\n\\nRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n\\n**Step 4: Commit**\\n\\n```bash\\ngit add cmd/entire/cli/commands/lifecycle.go\\ngit commit -m \\\"perf: instrument TurnStart and SessionStart handlers\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Task 7: Instrument manual_commit_hooks.go — PrepareCommitMsg\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — `PrepareCommitMsg()` (~lines 300-477)\\n\\n**Step 1: Add a root span and substep spans**\\n\\nPrepareCommitMsg is called directly by git (not via hook_registry), so it needs its own root span:\\n\\n```go\\nfunc (s *ManualCommitStrategy) PrepareCommitMsg(ctx context.Context, ...) error {\\n    ctx, span := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"prepare_commit_msg\\\")\\n    defer span.End()\\n\\n    // ... early exit checks (rebase/merge/squash) ...\\n\\n    ctx, sub := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"load_sessions\\\")\\n    // ... repository + session discovery ...\\n    sub.End()\\n\\n    ctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"get_staged_files\\\")\\n    // ... getStagedFiles() call ...\\n    sub.End()\\n\\n    ctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"content_overlap\\\")\\n    // ... content detection / transcript analysis ...\\n    sub.End()\\n\\n    ctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"write_trailer\\\")\\n    // ... message modification + trailer addition ...\\n    sub.End()\\n\\n    return nil\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Note:** The TTY confirmation (`askConfirmTTY`) should NOT be included inside a span — it blocks on user input and would skew timing. Place the `write_trailer` span only around the actual write logic.\\n\\nAdd import: `\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/perf\\\"`\\n\\n**Step 2: Run fmt, lint, and tests**\\n\\nRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n\\n**Step 3: Commit**\\n\\n```bash\\ngit add cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go\\ngit commit -m \\\"perf: instrument PrepareCommitMsg with substep spans\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Task 8: Instrument manual_commit_hooks.go — PostCommit\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — `PostCommit()` (~lines 721-835) and `postCommitProcessSession()` (~lines 840-994)\\n\\n**Step 1: Add root span + substeps to PostCommit**\\n\\n```go\\nfunc (s *ManualCommitStrategy) PostCommit(ctx context.Context, ...) error {\\n    ctx, span := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"post_commit\\\")\\n    defer span.End()\\n\\n    ctx, sub := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"load_sessions\\\")\\n    // ... open repo, get HEAD, parse trailer, find sessions ...\\n    sub.End()\\n\\n    ctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"resolve_git_objects\\\")\\n    // ... pre-resolve headTree, parentTree ...\\n    sub.End()\\n\\n    // Session processing loop — each session gets a Measure call\\n    for _, session := range sessions {\\n        span.Measure(\\\"process_session\\\", func() {\\n            postCommitProcessSession(ctx, ...)\\n        })\\n    }\\n\\n    ctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"cleanup_branches\\\")\\n    // ... shadow branch cleanup ...\\n    sub.End()\\n\\n    return nil\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Step 2: Add substeps inside postCommitProcessSession**\\n\\n```go\\nfunc (s *ManualCommitStrategy) postCommitProcessSession(ctx context.Context, ...) error {\\n    ctx, sub := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"resolve_shadow\\\")\\n    // ... resolve shadow branch ref + tree ...\\n    sub.End()\\n\\n    ctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"condense\\\")\\n    // ... state machine transition + CondenseSession call ...\\n    sub.End()\\n\\n    ctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"carry_forward\\\")\\n    // ... carry-forward computation + final state save ...\\n    sub.End()\\n\\n    return nil\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Step 3: Run fmt, lint, and tests**\\n\\nRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n\\n**Step 4: Commit**\\n\\n```bash\\ngit add cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go\\ngit commit -m \\\"perf: instrument PostCommit and session processing with spans\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Task 9: Instrument manual_commit_git.go — SaveStep\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_git.go` — `SaveStep()` (~lines 23-164)\\n\\n**Step 1: Add substep spans**\\n\\n```go\\nfunc (s *ManualCommitStrategy) SaveStep(ctx context.Context, sc StepContext) error {\\n    ctx, span := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"save_step\\\")\\n    defer span.End()\\n\\n    ctx, sub := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"load_session_state\\\")\\n    // ... load or initialize session state ...\\n    sub.End()\\n\\n    ctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"check_migration\\\")\\n    // ... check + migrate shadow branch ...\\n    sub.End()\\n\\n    ctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"write_checkpoint\\\")\\n    // ... store.WriteTemporary() — git tree building + commit ...\\n    sub.End()\\n\\n    ctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"update_state\\\")\\n    // ... update session state (StepCount, attributions, files, tokens) ...\\n    sub.End()\\n\\n    return nil\\n}\\n```\\n\\nAdd import: `\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/perf\\\"`\\n\\n**Step 2: Run fmt, lint, and tests**\\n\\nRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n\\n**Step 3: Commit**\\n\\n```bash\\ngit add cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_git.go\\ngit commit -m \\\"perf: instrument SaveStep with substep spans\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Task 10: Instrument PrePush\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/push_common.go` (or wherever `PrePush`/`pushSessionsBranchCommon` lives)\\n\\n**Step 1: Add substep spans**\\n\\n```go\\nfunc (s *ManualCommitStrategy) PrePush(ctx context.Context, ...) error {\\n    ctx, span := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"pre_push\\\")\\n    defer span.End()\\n\\n    span.Measure(\\\"push_checkpoint_branch\\\", func() {\\n        // ... pushSessionsBranchCommon() ...\\n    })\\n\\n    span.Measure(\\\"push_trails_branch\\\", func() {\\n        // ... PushTrailsBranch() ...\\n    })\\n\\n    return nil\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Step 2: Run fmt, lint, and tests**\\n\\nRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n\\n**Step 3: Commit**\\n\\n```bash\\ngit add cmd/entire/cli/strategy/push_common.go\\ngit commit -m \\\"perf: instrument PrePush with substep spans\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Task 11: Final verification and cleanup\\n\\n**Step 1: Run full test suite**\\n\\nRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\nExpected: All pass, no lint errors\\n\\n**Step 2: Manual smoke test**\\n\\nRun: `ENTIRE_LOG_LEVEL=debug entire hooks claude-code stop` (or whichever hook is convenient)\\nExpected: A `perf` log line appears in `.entire/logs/entire.log` with `op` and `steps.*_ms` fields\\n\\n**Step 3: Check for unused LogDuration import**\\n\\nIf `LogDuration` is no longer called in `hook_registry.go`, verify no dangling import of `\\\"time\\\"` or unused reference. The `logging.LogDuration` function should remain in the `logging` package (it may be used elsewhere), just not in `hook_registry.go`.\\n\\n**Step 4: Commit any final cleanups**\\n\\n```bash\\ngit add -A\\ngit commit -m \\\"perf: final cleanup after instrumentation\\\"\\n```\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":7809,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":71267,\"output_tokens\":6284,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":7809,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYhFQ1Gd7efQ24gpwP8uX\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"e7c38b74-ff4e-4652-a532-4dedd938d1c5\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T02:28:18.573Z\"}\n{\"type\":\"file-history-snapshot\",\"messageId\":\"e7c38b74-ff4e-4652-a532-4dedd938d1c5\",\"snapshot\":{\"messageId\":\"527a2c54-ce46-462f-b1ce-1b03fd6227e0\",\"trackedFileBackups\":{\"docs/plans/2026-03-03-perf-framework-design.md\":{\"backupFileName\":\"7b728ffc44247619@v2\",\"version\":2,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-04T01:02:00.254Z\"},\"docs/plans/2026-03-03-perf-framework-plan.md\":{\"backupFileName\":null,\"version\":1,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-04T02:28:18.610Z\"}},\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T01:02:00.254Z\"},\"isSnapshotUpdate\":true}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"e7c38b74-ff4e-4652-a532-4dedd938d1c5\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation\",\"sessionId\":\"2d62938d-a5d3-4bac-9d0f-bf8056