mportant:** The `ctx` returned from `perf.Start` must be used for subsequent calls so child spans nest correctly under the hook registry's root span. Add import for `\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/perf\\\"`.\\n\\n**Step 2: Run fmt, lint, and tests**\\n\\nRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n\\n**Step 3: Commit**\\n\\n```bash\\ngit add cmd/entire/cli/commands/lifecycle.go\\ngit commit -m \\\"perf: instrument TurnEnd handler with substep spans\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Task 6: Instrument lifecycle.go — TurnStart and SessionStart\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/commands/lifecycle.go` — `handleLifecycleTurnStart()` (~lines 119-154) and `handleLifecycleSessionStart()` (~lines 61-117)\\n\\n**Step 1: Add substep spans to TurnStart**\\n\\n```go\\n// In handleLifecycleTurnStart:\\nctx, sub := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"capture_file_state\\\")\\n// ... CapturePrePromptState() ...\\nsub.End()\\n\\nctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"init_session\\\")\\n// ... EnsureSetup() + InitializeSession() ...\\nsub.End()\\n```\\n\\n**Step 2: Add substep spans to SessionStart**\\n\\n```go\\n// In handleLifecycleSessionStart:\\nctx, sub := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"check_concurrent\\\")\\n// ... concurrent session check logic ...\\nsub.End()\\n\\nctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"show_banner\\\")\\n// ... banner display ...\\nsub.End()\\n```\\n\\n**Step 3: Run fmt, lint, and tests**\\n\\nRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n\\n**Step 4: Commit**\\n\\n```bash\\ngit add cmd/entire/cli/commands/lifecycle.go\\ngit commit -m \\\"perf: instrument TurnStart and SessionStart handlers\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Task 7: Instrument manual_commit_hooks.go — PrepareCommitMsg\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — `PrepareCommitMsg()` (~lines 300-477)\\n\\n**Step 1: Add a root span and substep spans**\\n\\nPrepareCommitMsg is called directly by git (not via hook_registry), so it needs its own root span:\\n\\n```go\