serType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation\",\"sessionId\":\"2d62938d-a5d3-4bac-9d0f-bf8056720e6d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"performance-logging-investigation\",\"slug\":\"wiggly-weaving-crayon\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01DoZWArH37h92UD7E862M1S\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01VLDMkiwr8uJ1nSsrwHYwKm\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation/docs/plans/2026-03-03-perf-framework-plan.md\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":2832,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":85701,\"output_tokens\":470,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":2832,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYiXtyNTCDCxBeRXS5dg9\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"829b072b-6d16-4259-b1fd-b5114b1d6f9f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T18:43:51.259Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"829b072b-6d16-4259-b1fd-b5114b1d6f9f\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation\",\"sessionId\":\"2d62938d-a5d3-4bac-9d0f-bf8056720e6d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"performance-logging-investigation\",\"slug\":\"wiggly-weaving-crayon\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Read\",\"command\":\"callback\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01VLDMkiwr8uJ1nSsrwHYwKm\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_01VLDMkiwr8uJ1nSsrwHYwKm\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T18:43:51.289Z\",\"uuid\":\"4baa45e6-46da-4de0-b902-e2afb30d37cb\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"829b072b-6d16-4259-b1fd-b5114b1d6f9f\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation\",\"sessionId\":\"2d62938d-a5d3-4bac-9d0f-bf8056720e6d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"performance-logging-investigation\",\"slug\":\"wiggly-weaving-crayon\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01VLDMkiwr8uJ1nSsrwHYwKm\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Performance Measurement Framework Implementation Plan\\n     2→\\n     3→> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\\n     4→\\n     5→**Goal:** Add a reusable `perf` package with span-based timing that instruments all hooks impacting git workflow and agent lifecycle.\\n     6→\\n     7→**Architecture:** Context-propagated spans that nest automatically. Root spans emit a single DEBUG log line via the existing `logging` package. The `perf` package has no external dependencies — just stdlib + the `logging` package.\\n     8→\\n     9→**Tech Stack:** Go stdlib (`context`, `time`, `log/slog`), existing `cmd/entire/cli/logging` package.\\n    10→\\n    11→**Design Doc:** `docs/plans/2026-03-03-perf-framework-design.md`\\n    12→\\n    13→---\\n    14→\\n    15→### Task 1: Create `perf` package — context.go\\n    16→\\n    17→**Files:**\\n    18→- Create: `cmd/entire/cli/perf/context.go`\\n    19→\\n    20→**Step 1: Write context.go**\\n    21→\\n    22→This file stores/retrieves spans from context. Follow the same pattern as `cmd/entire/cli/logging/context.go`.\\n    23→\\n    24→```go\\n    25→package perf\\n    26→\\n    27→import \\\"context\\\"\\n    28→\\n    29→type contextKey struct{}\\n    30→\\n    31→// spanFromContext retrieves the current span from context, or nil if none.\\n    32→func spanFromContext(ctx context.Context) *Span {\\n    33→\\tif v := ctx.Value(contextKey{}); v != nil {\\n    34→\\t\\tif s, ok := v.(*Span); ok {\\n    35→\\t\\t\\treturn s\\n    36→\\t\\t}\\n    37→\\t}\\n    38→\\treturn nil\\n    39→}\\n    40→\\n    41→// contextWithSpan returns a new context with the span stored.\\n    42→func contextWithSpan(ctx context.Context, s *Span) context.Context {\\n    43→\\treturn context.WithValue(ctx, contextKey{}, s)\\n    44→}\\n    45→```\\n    46→\\n    47→**Step 2: Commit**\\n    48→\\n    49→```bash\\n    50→git add cmd/entire/cli/perf/context.go\\n    51→git commit -m \\\"perf: add context propagation for spans\\\"\\n    52→```\\n    53→\\n    54→---\\n    55→\\n    56→### Task 2: Create `perf` package — span.go\\n    57→\\n    58→**Files:**\\n    59→- Create: `cmd/entire/cli/perf/span.go`\\n    60→\\n    61→**Step 1: Write span.go**\\n    62→\\n    63→The core Span type with Start(), End(), and Measure(). Root spans log via `logging.Debug()` on End(). Child spans record duration only.\\n    64→\\n    65→```go\\n    66→package perf\\n    67→\\n    68→import (\\n    69→\\t\\\"context\\\"\\n    70→\\t\\\"fmt\\\"\\n    71→\\t\\\"log/slog\\\"\\n    72→\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n    73→\\n    74→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/logging\\\"\\n    75→)\\n    76→\\n    77→// Span tracks timing for an operation and its substeps.\\n    78→type Span struct {\\n    79→\\tname     string\\n    80→\\tstart    time.Time\\n    81→\\tparent   *Span\\n    82→\\tchildren []*Span\\n    83→\\tduration time.Duration\\n    84→\\tattrs    []slog.Attr\\n    85→\\tctx      context.Context\\n    86→\\tended    bool\\n    87→}\\n    88→\\n    89→// Start begins a new span. If ctx already has a span, the new one becomes a child.\\n    90→// Returns the updated context and the span. Call span.End() when the operation completes.\\n    91→func Start(ctx context.Context, name string, attrs ...slog.Attr) (context.Context, *Span) {\\n    92→\\tparent := spanFromContext(ctx)\\n    93→\\ts := &Span{\\n    94→\\t\\tname:   name,\\n    95→\\t\\tstart:  time.Now(),\\n    96→\\t\\tparent: parent,\\n    97→\\t\\tattrs:  attrs,\\n    98→\\t\\tctx:    ctx,\\n    99→\\t}\\n   100→\\tif parent != nil {\\n   101→\\t\\tparent.children = append(parent.children, s)\\n   102→\\t}\\n   103→\\treturn contextWithSpan(ctx, s), s\\n   104→}\\n   105→\\n   106→// End completes the span. For root spans, emits a single DEBUG log line\\n   107→// with the full timing tree. For child spans, records the duration only.\\n   108→// Safe to call multiple times — subsequent calls are no-ops.\\n   109→func (s *Span) End() {\\n   110→\\tif s.ended {\\n   111→\\t\\treturn\\n   112→\\t}\\n   113→\\ts.ended = true\\n   114→\\ts.duration = time.Since(s.start)\\n   115→\\n   116→\\t// Only root spans emit log output\\n   117→\\tif s.parent != nil {\\n   118→\\t\\treturn\\n   119→\\t}\\n   120→\\n   121→\\t// Build log attributes: op, duration_ms, then child step durations\\n   122→\\tattrs := make([]any, 0, 3+len(s.children)+len(s.attrs))\\n   123→\\tattrs = append(attrs, slog.String(\\\"component\\\", \\\"perf\\\"))\\n   124→\\tattrs = append(attrs, slog.String(\\\"op\\\", s.name))\\n   125→\\tattrs = append(attrs, slog.Int64(\\\"duration_ms\\\", s.duration.Milliseconds()))\\n   126→\\n   127→\\t// Add child step durations as flat keys\\n   128→\\tfor _, child := range s.children {\\n   129→\\t\\t// Auto-end children that weren't explicitly ended\\n   130→\\t\\tif !child.ended {\\n   131→\\t\\t\\tchild.ended = true\\n   132→\\t\\t\\tchild.duration = time.Since(child.start)\\n   133→\\t\\t}\\n   134→\\t\\tkey := fmt.Sprintf(\\\"steps.%s_ms\\\", child.name)\\n   135→\\t\\tattrs = append(attrs, slog.Int64(key, child.duration.Milliseconds()))\\n   136→\\t}\\n   137→\\n   138→\\t// Add any extra attributes from Start()\\n   139→\\tfor _, a := range s.attrs {\\n   140→\\t\\tattrs = append(attrs, a)\\n   141→\\t}\\n   142→\\n   143→\\tlogging.Debug(s.ctx, \\\"perf\\\", attrs...)\\n   144→}\\n   145→\\n   146→// Measure times a function as a child substep of this span.\\n   147→func (s *Span) Measure(name string, fn func()) {\\n   148→\\t_, child := Start(s.ctx, name)\\n   149→\\tfn()\\n   150→\\tchild.End()\\n   151→}\\n   152→```\\n   153→\\n   154→**Step 2: Run fmt and lint**\\n   155→\\n   156→Run: `mise run fmt && mise run lint`\\n   157→\\n   158→**Step 3: Commit**\\n   159→\\n   160→```bash\\n   161→git add cmd/entire/cli/perf/span.go\\n   162→git commit -m \\\"perf: add Span type with Start/End/Measure API\\\"\\n   163→```\\n   164→\\n   165→---\\n   166→\\n   167→### Task 3: Write unit tests for `perf` package\\n   168→\\n   169→**Files:**\\n   170→- Create: `cmd/entire/cli/perf/span_test.go`\\n   171→\\n   172→**Step 1: Write span_test.go**\\n   173→\\n   174→Tests verify: basic span timing, child nesting, Measure helper, double-End safety, auto-end of children, and log output format. The tests use a similar pattern to `cmd/entire/cli/logging/logger_test.go` — writing to a buffer via the logging package then parsing JSON.\\n   175→\\n   176→```go\\n   177→package perf\\n   178→\\n   179→import (\\n   180→\\t\\\"context\\\"\\n   181→\\t\\\"testing\\\"\\n   182→\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n   183→)\\n   184→\\n   185→func TestStart_CreatesRootSpan(t *testing.T) {\\n   186→\\tt.Parallel()\\n   187→\\tctx := context.Background()\\n   188→\\n   189→\\tctx, span := Start(ctx, \\\"test_op\\\")\\n   190→\\tif span == nil {\\n   191→\\t\\tt.Fatal(\\\"Start() returned nil span\\\")\\n   192→\\t}\\n   193→\\tif span.name != \\\"test_op\\\" {\\n   194→\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"span.name = %q, want %q\\\", span.name, \\\"test_op\\\")\\n   195→\\t}\\n   196→\\tif span.parent != nil {\\n   197→\\t\\tt.Error(\\\"root span should have nil parent\\\")\\n   198→\\t}\\n   199→\\n   200→\\t// Verify span is in context\\n   201→\\tgot := spanFromContext(ctx)\\n   202→\\tif got != span {\\n   203→\\t\\tt.Error(\\\"spanFromContext should return the span set by Start\\\")\\n   204→\\t}\\n   205→\\n   206→\\tspan.End()\\n   207→}\\n   208→\\n   209→func TestStart_NestsChildSpan(t *testing.T) {\\n   210→\\tt.Parallel()\\n   211→\\tctx := context.Background()\\n   212→\\n   213→\\tctx, parent := Start(ctx, \\\"parent\\\")\\n   214→\\t_, child := Start(ctx, \\\"child\\\")\\n   215→\\n   216→\\tif child.parent != parent {\\n   217→\\t\\tt.Error(\\\"child span should reference parent\\\")\\n   218→\\t}\\n   219→\\tif len(parent.children) != 1 {\\n   220→\\t\\tt.Fatalf(\\\"parent should have 1 child, got %d\\\", len(parent.children))\\n   221→\\t}\\n   222→\\tif parent.children[0] != child {\\n   223→\\t\\tt.Error(\\\"parent.children[0] should be the child span\\\")\\n   224→\\t}\\n   225→\\n   226→\\tchild.End()\\n   227→\\tparent.End()\\n   228→}\\n   229→\\n   230→func TestEnd_RecordsDuration(t *testing.T) {\\n   231→\\tt.Parallel()\\n   232→\\tctx := context.Background()\\n   233→\\n   234→\\t_, span := Start(ctx, \\\"timed_op\\\")\\n   235→\\ttime.Sleep(10 * time.Millisecond)\\n   236→\\tspan.End()\\n   237→\\n   238→\\tif span.duration < 10*time.Millisecond {\\n   239→\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"span.duration = %v, want >= 10ms\\\", span.duration)\\n   240→\\t}\\n   241→}\\n   242→\\n   243→func TestEnd_Idempotent(t *testing.T) {\\n   244→\\tt.Parallel()\\n   245→\\tctx := context.Background()\\n   246→\\n   247→\\t_, span := Start(ctx, \\\"double_end\\\")\\n   248→\\ttime.Sleep(10 * time.Millisecond)\\n   249→\\tspan.End()\\n   250→\\n   251→\\tfirstDuration := span.duration\\n   252→\\n   253→\\t// Second End should be a no-op\\n   254→\\ttime.Sleep(10 * time.Millisecond)\\n   255→\\tspan.End()\\n   256→\\n   257→\\tif span.duration != firstDuration {\\n   258→\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"second End() changed duration from %v to %v\\\", firstDuration, span.duration)\\n   259→\\t}\\n   260→}\\n   261→\\n   262→func TestEnd_AutoEndsChildren(t *testing.T) {\\n   263→\\tt.Parallel()\\n   264→\\tctx := context.Background()\\n   265→\\n   266→\\tctx, parent := Start(ctx, \\\"parent\\\")\\n   267→\\t_, child := Start(ctx, \\\"child\\\")\\n   268→\\n   269→\\t// Don't explicitly end child\\n   270→\\ttime.Sleep(10 * time.Millisecond)\\n   271→\\tparent.End()\\n   272→\\n   273→\\tif !child.ended {\\n   274→\\t\\tt.Error(\\\"child should be auto-ended when parent ends\\\")\\n   275→\\t}\\n   276→\\tif child.duration == 0 {\\n   277→\\t\\tt.Error(\\\"child should have non-zero duration after auto-end\\\")\\n   278→\\t}\\n   279→}\\n   280→\\n   281→func TestMeasure_TimesFunction(t *testing.T) {\\n   282→\\tt.Parallel()\\n   283→\\tctx := context.Background()\\n   284→\\n   285→\\t_, span := Start(ctx, \\\"parent\\\")\\n   286→\\n   287→\\tspan.Measure(\\\"substep\\\", func() {\\n   288→\\t\\ttime.Sleep(10 * time.Millisecond)\\n   289→\\t})\\n   290→\\n   291→\\tspan.End()\\n   292→\\n   293→\\tif len(span.children) != 1 {\\n   294→\\t\\tt.Fatalf(\\\"expected 1 child from Measure, got %d\\\", len(span.children))\\n   295→\\t}\\n   296→\\tchild := span.children[0]\\n   297→\\tif child.name != \\\"substep\\\" {\\n   298→\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"child.name = %q, want %q\\\", child.name, \\\"substep\\\")\\n   299→\\t}\\n   300→\\tif child.duration < 10*time.Millisecond {\\n   301→\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"child.duration = %v, want >= 10ms\\\", child.duration)\\n   302→\\t}\\n   303→}\\n   304→\\n   305→func TestSpanFromContext_ReturnsNilWhenEmpty(t *testing.T) {\\n   306→\\tt.Parallel()\\n   307→\\tctx := context.Background()\\n   308→\\n   309→\\tif got := spanFromContext(ctx); got != nil {\\n   310→\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"spanFromContext on empty context = %v, want nil\\\", got)\\n   311→\\t}\\n   312→}\\n   313→\\n   314→func TestStart_MultipleChildren(t *testing.T) {\\n   315→\\tt.Parallel()\\n   316→\\tctx := context.Background()\\n   317→\\n   318→\\tctx, parent := Start(ctx, \\\"parent\\\")\\n   319→\\n   320→\\tctx2, child1 := Start(ctx, \\\"child1\\\")\\n   321→\\t_ = ctx2\\n   322→\\tchild1.End()\\n   323→\\n   324→\\tctx3, child2 := Start(ctx, \\\"child2\\\")\\n   325→\\t_ = ctx3\\n   326→\\tchild2.End()\\n   327→\\n   328→\\tparent.End()\\n   329→\\n   330→\\tif len(parent.children) != 2 {\\n   331→\\t\\tt.Fatalf(\\\"expected 2 children, got %d\\\", len(parent.children))\\n   332→\\t}\\n   333→\\tif parent.children[0].name != \\\"child1\\\" {\\n   334→\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"first child name = %q, want %q\\\", parent.children[0].name, \\\"child1\\\")\\n   335→\\t}\\n   336→\\tif parent.children[1].name != \\\"child2\\\" {\\n   337→\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"second child name = %q, want %q\\\", parent.children[1].name, \\\"child2\\\")\\n   338→\\t}\\n   339→}\\n   340→```\\n   341→\\n   342→**Step 2: Run the tests**\\n   343→\\n   344→Run: `mise run test -- -run TestStart -v ./cmd/entire/cli/perf/`\\n   345→Expected: All tests PASS\\n   346→\\n   347→**Step 3: Run fmt, lint, and full test suite**\\n   348→\\n   349→Run: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n   350→\\n   351→**Step 4: Commit**\\n   352→\\n   353→```bash\\n   354→git add cmd/entire/cli/perf/span_test.go\\n   355→git commit -m \\\"perf: add unit tests for span API\\\"\\n   356→```\\n   357→\\n   358→---\\n   359→\\n   360→### Task 4: Instrument hook_registry.go — replace LogDuration with root span\\n   361→\\n   362→**Files:**\\n   363→- Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/commands/hook_registry.go` — the `newAgentHookVerbCmdWithLogging()` function\\n   364→\\n   365→**Step 1: Replace LogDuration with perf.Start/End**\\n   366→\\n   367→In `newAgentHookVerbCmdWithLogging()`, find the existing timing code (around lines 109-161):\\n   368→\\n   369→```go\\n   370→// Current code (approximate):\\n   371→start := time.Now()\\n   372→// ... hook logic ...\\n   373→logging.LogDuration(ctx, slog.LevelDebug, \\\"hook completed\\\", start,\\n   374→    slog.String(\\\"hook\\\", hookName),\\n   375→    slog.String(\\\"hook_type\\\", hookType),\\n   376→    slog.Bool(\\\"success\\\", hookErr == nil))\\n   377→```\\n   378→\\n   379→Replace with:\\n   380→\\n   381→```go\\n   382→ctx, span := perf.Start(ctx, hookName,\\n   383→    slog.String(\\\"hook_type\\\", hookType))\\n   384→defer span.End()\\n   385→// ... rest of hook logic (remove old start/LogDuration) ...\\n   386→```\\n   387→\\n   388→The `span.End()` in defer will emit the root-level perf log with any child spans added downstream by lifecycle handlers and strategy methods.\\n   389→\\n   390→**Important:** Add the import `\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/perf\\\"` and remove unused `\\\"time\\\"` import if no longer needed.\\n   391→\\n   392→**Step 2: Run fmt, lint, and tests**\\n   393→\\n   394→Run: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n   395→\\n   396→**Step 3: Commit**\\n   397→\\n   398→```bash\\n   399→git add cmd/entire/cli/commands/hook_registry.go\\n   400→git commit -m \\\"perf: replace LogDuration with root perf span in hook registry\\\"\\n   401→```\\n   402→\\n   403→---\\n   404→\\n   405→### Task 5: Instrument lifecycle.go — TurnEnd substeps\\n   406→\\n   407→**Files:**\\n   408→- Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/commands/lifecycle.go` — `handleLifecycleTurnEnd()` (lines ~160-419)\\n   409→\\n   410→**Step 1: Add child spans for each major substep**\\n   411→\\n   412→The TurnEnd handler has these sequential phases. Wrap each with `perf.Start`/`End`:\\n   413→\\n   414→1. **prepare_transcript** (~lines 184-189): `PrepareTranscript()` call\\n   415→2. **copy_transcript** (~lines 201-219): Creating metadata dir + copying transcript file\\n   416→3. **extract_metadata** (~lines 223-276): Extracting prompts, summary, modified files\\n   417→4. **write_session_files** (~lines 278-294): Writing prompts/summary/context files\\n   418→5. **detect_changes** (~lines 318-337): Git status + file change detection\\n   419→6. **normalize_paths** (~lines 339-355): Filter and normalize file paths\\n   420→7. **save_step** (~lines 360-404): Building StepContext + calling strategy.SaveStep()\\n   421→\\n   422→Pattern for each substep:\\n   423→\\n   424→```go\\n   425→ctx, sub := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"prepare_transcript\\\")\\n   426→// ... existing code for this substep ...\\n   427→sub.End()\\n   428→```\\n   429→\\n   430→**Important:** The `ctx` returned from `perf.Start` must be used for subsequent calls so child spans nest correctly under the hook registry's root span. Add import for `\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/perf\\\"`.\\n   431→\\n   432→**Step 2: Run fmt, lint, and tests**\\n   433→\\n   434→Run: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n   435→\\n   436→**Step 3: Commit**\\n   437→\\n   438→```bash\\n   439→git add cmd/entire/cli/commands/lifecycle.go\\n   440→git commit -m \\\"perf: instrument TurnEnd handler with substep spans\\\"\\n   441→```\\n   442→\\n   443→---\\n   444→\\n   445→### Task 6: Instrument lifecycle.go — TurnStart and SessionStart\\n   446→\\n   447→**Files:**\\n   448→- Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/commands/lifecycle.go` — `handleLifecycleTurnStart()` (~lines 119-154) and `handleLifecycleSessionStart()` (~lines 61-117)\\n   449→\\n   450→**Step 1: Add substep spans to TurnStart**\\n   451→\\n   452→```go\\n   453→// In handleLifecycleTurnStart:\\n   454→ctx, sub := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"capture_file_state\\\")\\n   455→// ... CapturePrePromptState() ...\\n   456→sub.End()\\n   457→\\n   458→ctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"init_session\\\")\\n   459→// ... EnsureSetup() + InitializeSession() ...\\n   460→sub.End()\\n   461→```\\n   462→\\n   463→**Step 2: Add substep spans to SessionStart**\\n   464→\\n   465→```go\\n   466→// In handleLifecycleSessionStart:\\n   467→ctx, sub := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"check_concurrent\\\")\\n   468→// ... concurrent session check logic ...\\n   469→sub.End()\\n   470→\\n   471→ctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"show_banner\\\")\\n   472→// ... banner display ...\\n   473→sub.End()\\n   474→```\\n   475→\\n   476→**Step 3: Run fmt, lint, and tests**\\n   477→\\n   478→Run: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n   479→\\n   480→**Step 4: Commit**\\n   481→\\n   482→```bash\\n   483→git add cmd/entire/cli/commands/lifecycle.go\\n   484→git commit -m \\\"perf: instrument TurnStart and SessionStart handlers\\\"\\n   485→```\\n   486→\\n   487→---\\n   488→\\n   489→### Task 7: Instrument manual_commit_hooks.go — PrepareCommitMsg\\n   490→\\n   491→**Files:**\\n   492→- Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — `PrepareCommitMsg()` (~lines 300-477)\\n   493→\\n   494→**Step 1: Add a root span and substep spans**\\n   495→\\n   496→PrepareCommitMsg is called directly by git (not via hook_registry), so it needs its own root span:\\n   497→\\n   498→```go\\n   499→func (s *ManualCommitStrategy) PrepareCommitMsg(ctx context.Context, ...) error {\\n   500→    ctx, span := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"prepare_commit_msg\\\")\\n   501→    defer span.End()\\n   502→\\n   503→    // ... early exit checks (rebase/merge/squash) ...\\n   504→\\n   505→    ctx, sub := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"load_sessions\\\")\\n   506→    // ... repository + session discovery ...\\n   507→    sub.End()\\n   508→\\n   509→    ctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"get_staged_files\\\")\\n   510→    // ... getStagedFiles() call ...\\n   511→    sub.End()\\n   512→\\n   513→    ctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"content_overlap\\\")\\n   514→    // ... content detection / transcript analysis ...\\n   515→    sub.End()\\n   516→\\n   517→    ctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"write_trailer\\\")\\n   518→    // ... message modification + trailer addition ...\\n   519→    sub.End()\\n   520→\\n   521→    return nil\\n   522→}\\n   523→```\\n   524→\\n   525→**Note:** The TTY confirmation (`askConfirmTTY`) should NOT be included inside a span — it blocks on user input and would skew timing. Place the `write_trailer` span only around the actual write logic.\\n   526→\\n   527→Add import: `\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/perf\\\"`\\n   528→\\n   529→**Step 2: Run fmt, lint, and tests**\\n   530→\\n   531→Run: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n   532→\\n   533→**Step 3: Commit**\\n   534→\\n   535→```bash\\n   536→git add cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go\\n   537→git commit -m \\\"perf: instrument PrepareCommitMsg with substep spans\\\"\\n   538→```\\n   539→\\n   540→---\\n   541→\\n   542→### Task 8: Instrument manual_commit_hooks.go — PostCommit\\n   543→\\n   544→**Files:**\\n   545→- Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — `PostCommit()` (~lines 721-835) and `postCommitProcessSession()` (~lines 840-994)\\n   546→\\n   547→**Step 1: Add root span + substeps to PostCommit**\\n   548→\\n   549→```go\\n   550→func (s *ManualCommitStrategy) PostCommit(ctx context.Context, ...) error {\\n   551→    ctx, span := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"post_commit\\\")\\n   552→    defer span.End()\\n   553→\\n   554→    ctx, sub := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"load_sessions\\\")\\n   555→    // ... open repo, get HEAD, parse trailer, find sessions ...\\n   556→    sub.End()\\n   557→\\n   558→    ctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"resolve_git_objects\\\")\\n   559→    // ... pre-resolve headTree, parentTree ...\\n   560→    sub.End()\\n   561→\\n   562→    // Session processing loop — each session gets a Measure call\\n   563→    for _, session := range sessions {\\n   564→        span.Measure(\\\"process_session\\\", func() {\\n   565→            postCommitProcessSession(ctx, ...)\\n   566→        })\\n   567→    }\\n   568→\\n   569→    ctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"cleanup_branches\\\")\\n   570→    // ... shadow branch cleanup ...\\n   571→    sub.End()\\n   572→\\n   573→    return nil\\n   574→}\\n   575→```\\n   576→\\n   577→**Step 2: Add substeps inside postCommitProcessSession**\\n   578→\\n   579→```go\\n   580→func (s *ManualCommitStrategy) postCommitProcessSession(ctx context.Context, ...) error {\\n   581→    ctx, sub := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"resolve_shadow\\\")\\n   582→    // ... resolve shadow branch ref + tree ...\\n   583→    sub.End()\\n   584→\\n   585→    ctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"condense\\\")\\n   586→    // ... state machine transition + CondenseSession call ...\\n   587→    sub.End()\\n   588→\\n   589→    ctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"carry_forward\\\")\\n   590→    // ... carry-forward computation + final state save ...\\n   591→    sub.End()\\n   592→\\n   593→    return nil\\n   594→}\\n   595→```\\n   596→\\n   597→**Step 3: Run fmt, lint, and tests**\\n   598→\\n   599→Run: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n   600→\\n   601→**Step 4: Commit**\\n   602→\\n   603→```bash\\n   604→git add cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go\\n   605→git commit -m \\\"perf: instrument PostCommit and session processing with spans\\\"\\n   606→```\\n   607→\\n   608→---\\n   609→\\n   610→### Task 9: Instrument manual_commit_git.go — SaveStep\\n   611→\\n   612→**Files:**\\n   613→- Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_git.go` — `SaveStep()` (~lines 23-164)\\n   614→\\n   615→**Step 1: Add substep spans**\\n   616→\\n   617→```go\\n   618→func (s *ManualCommitStrategy) SaveStep(ctx context.Context, sc StepContext) error {\\n   619→    ctx, span := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"save_step\\\")\\n   620→    defer span.End()\\n   621→\\n   622→    ctx, sub := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"load_session_state\\\")\\n   623→    // ... load or initialize session state ...\\n   624→    sub.End()\\n   625→\\n   626→    ctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"check_migration\\\")\\n   627→    // ... check + migrate shadow branch ...\\n   628→    sub.End()\\n   629→\\n   630→    ctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"write_checkpoint\\\")\\n   631→    // ... store.WriteTemporary() — git tree building + commit ...\\n   632→    sub.End()\\n   633→\\n   634→    ctx, sub = perf.Start(ctx, \\\"update_state\\\")\\n   635→    // ... update session state (StepCount, attributions, files, tokens) ...\\n   636→    sub.End()\\n   637→\\n   638→    return nil\\n   639→}\\n   640→```\\n   641→\\n   642→Add import: `\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/perf\\\"`\\n   643→\\n   644→**Step 2: Run fmt, lint, and tests**\\n   645→\\n   646→Run: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n   647→\\n   648→**Step 3: Commit**\\n   649→\\n   650→```bash\\n   651→git add cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_git.go\\n   652→git commit -m \\\"perf: instrument SaveStep with substep spans\\\"\\n   653→```\\n   654→\\n   655→---\\n   656→\\n   657→### Task 10: Instrument PrePush\\n   658→\\n   659→**Files:**\\n   660→- Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/push_common.go` (or wherever `PrePush`/`pushSessionsBranchCommon` lives)\\n   661→\\n   662→**Step 1: Add substep spans**\\n   663→\\n   664→```go\\n   665→func (s *ManualCommitStrategy) PrePush(ctx context.Context, ...) error {\\n   666→    ctx, span := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"pre_push\\\")\\n   667→    defer span.End()\\n   668→\\n   669→    span.Measure(\\\"push_checkpoint_branch\\\", func() {\\n   670→        // ... pushSessionsBranchCommon() ...\\n   671→    })\\n   672→\\n   673→    span.Measure(\\\"push_trails_branch\\\", func() {\\n   674→        // ... PushTrailsBranch() ...\\n   675→    })\\n   676→\\n   677→    return nil\\n   678→}\\n   679→```\\n   680→\\n   681→**Step 2: Run fmt, lint, and tests**\\n   682→\\n   683→Run: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n   684→\\n   685→**Step 3: Commit**\\n   686→\\n   687→```bash\\n   688→git add cmd/entire/cli/strategy/push_common.go\\n   689→git commit -m \\\"perf: instrument PrePush with substep spans\\\"\\n   690→```\\n   691→\\n   692→---\\n   693→\\n   694→### Task 11: Final verification and cleanup\\n   695→\\n   696→**Step 1: Run full test suite**\\n   697→\\n   698→Run: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n   699→Expected: All pass, no lint errors\\n   700→\\n   701→**Step 2: Manual smoke test**\\n   702→\\n   703→Run: `ENTIRE_LOG_LEVEL=debug entire hooks claude-code stop` (or whichever hook is convenient)\\n   704→Expected: A `perf` log line appears in `.entire/logs/entire.log` with `op` and `steps.*_ms` fields\\n   705→\\n   706→**Step 3: Check for unused LogDuration import**\\n   707→\\n   708→If `LogDuration` is no longer called in `hook_registry.go`, verify no dangling import of `\\\"time\\\"` or unused reference. The `logging.LogDuration` function should remain in the `logging` package (it may be used elsewhere), just not in `hook_registry.go`.\\n   709→\\n   710→**Step 4: Commit any final cleanups**\\n   711→\\n   712→```bash\\n   713→git add -A\\n   714→git commit -m \\\"perf: final cleanup after instrumentation\\\"\\n   715→```\\n   716→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"6f29fdaa-3277-44cd-8e05-62a0c1764551\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T18:43:51.289Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation/docs/plans/2026-03-03-perf-framework-plan.md\",\"content\":\"# Performance Measurement Framework Implementation Plan\\n\\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\\n\\n**Goal:** Add a reusable `perf` package with span-based timing that instruments all hooks impacting git workflow and agent lifecycle.\\n\\n**Architecture:** Context-propagated spans that nest automatically. Root spans emit a single DEBUG log line via the existing `logging` package. The `perf` package has no external dependencies — just stdlib + the `logging` package.\\n\\n**Tech Stack:** Go stdlib (`context`, `time`, `log/slog`), existing `cmd/entire/cli/logging` package.\\n\\n**Design Doc:** `docs/plans/2026-03-03-perf-framework-design.md`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Task 1: Create `perf` package — context.go\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- Create: `cmd/entire/cli/perf/context.go`\\n\\n**Step 1: Write context.go**\\n\\nThis file stores/retrieves spans from context. Follow the same pattern as `cmd/entire/cli/logging/context.go`.\\n\\n```go\\npackage perf\\n\\nimport \\\"context\\\"\\n\\ntype contextKey struct{}\\n\\n// spanFromContext retrieves the current span from context, or nil if none.\\nfunc spanFromContext(ctx context.Context) *Span {\\n\\tif v := ctx.Value(contextKey{}); v != nil {\\n\\t\\tif s, ok := v.(*Span); ok {\\n\\t\\t\\treturn s\\n\\t\\t}\\n\\t}\\n\\treturn nil\\n}\\n\\n// contextWithSpan returns a new context with the span stored.\\nfunc contextWithSpan(ctx context.Context, s *Span) context.Context {\\n\\treturn context.WithValue(ctx, contextKey{}, s)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Step 2: Commit**\\n\\n```bash\\ngit add cmd/entire/cli/perf/context.go\\ngit commit -m \\\"perf: add context propagation for spans\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Task 2: Create `perf` package — span.go\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- Create: `cmd/entire/cli/perf/span.go`\\n\\n**Step 1: Write span.go**\\n\\nThe core Span type with Start(), End(), and Measure(). Root spans log via `logging.Debug()` on End(). Child spans record duration only.\\n\\n```go\\npackage perf\\n\\nimport (\\n\\t\\\"context\\\"\\n\\t\\\"fmt\\\"\\n\\t\\\"log/slog\\\"\\n\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n\\n\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/logging\\\"\\n)\\n\\n// Span tracks timing for an operation and its substeps.\\ntype Span struct {\\n\\tname     string\\n\\tstart    time.Time\\n\\tparent   *Span\\n\\tchildren []*Span\\n\\tduration time.Duration\\n\\tattrs    []slog.Attr\\n\\tctx      context.Context\\n\\tended    bool\\n}\\n\\n// Start begins a new span. If ctx already has a span, the new one becomes a child.\\n// Returns the updated context and the span. Call span.End() when the operation completes.\\nfunc Start(ctx context.Context, name string, attrs ...slog.Attr) (context.Context, *Span) {\\n\\tparent := spanFromContext(ctx)\\n\\ts := &Span{\\n\\t\\tname:   name,\\n\\t\\tstart:  time.Now(),\\n\\t\\tparent: parent,\\n\\t\\tattrs:  attrs,\\n\\t\\tctx:    ctx,\\n\\t}\\n\\tif parent != nil {\\n\\t\\tparent.children = append(parent.children, s)\\n\\t}\\n\\treturn contextWithSpan(ctx, s), s\\n}\\n\\n// End completes the span. For root spans, emits a single DEBUG log line\\n// with the full timing tree. For child spans, records the duration only.\\n// Safe to call multiple times — subsequent calls are no-ops.\\nfunc (s *Span) End() {\\n\\tif s.ended {\\n\\t\\treturn\\n\\t}\\n\\ts.ended = true\\n\\ts.duration = time.Since(s.start)\\n\\n\\t// Only root spans emit log output\\n\\tif s.parent != nil {\\n\\t\\treturn\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\t// Build log attributes: op, duration_ms, then child step durations\\n\\tattrs := make([]any, 0, 3+len(s.children)+len(s.attrs))\\n\\tattrs = append(attrs, slog.String(\\\"component\\\", \\\"perf\\\"))\\n\\tattrs = append(attrs, slog.String(\\\"op\\\", s.name))\\n\\tattrs = append(attrs, slog.Int64(\\\"duration_ms\\\", s.duration.Milliseconds()))\\n\\n\\t// Add child step durations as flat keys\\n\\tfor _, child := range s.children {\\n\\t\\t// Auto-end children that weren't explicitly ended\\n\\t\\tif !child.ended {\\n\\t\\t\\tchild.ended = true\\n\\t\\t\\tchild.duration = time.Since(child.start)\\n\\t\\t}\\n\\t\\tkey := fmt.Sprintf(\\\"steps.%s_ms\\\", child.name)\\n\\t\\tattrs = append(attrs, slog.Int64(key, child.duration.Milliseconds()))\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\t// Add any extra attributes from Start()\\n\\tfor _, a := range s.attrs {\\n\\t\\tattrs = append(attrs, a)\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\tlogging.Debug(s.ctx, \\\"perf\\\", attrs...)\\n}\\n\\n// Measure times a function as a child substep of this span.\\nfunc (s *Span) Measure(name string, fn func()) {\\n\\t_, child := Start(s.ctx, name)\\n\\tfn()\\n\\tchild.End()\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Step 2: Run fmt and lint**\\n\\nRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint`\\n\\n**Step 3: Commit**\\n\\n```bash\\ngit add cmd/entire/cli/perf/span.go\\ngit commit -m \\\"perf: add Span type with Start/End/Measure API\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Task 3: Write unit tests for `perf` package\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- Create: `cmd/entire/cli/perf/span_test.go`\\n\\n**Step 1: Write span_test.go**\\n\\nTests verify: basic span timing, child nesting, Measure helper, double-End safety, auto-end of children, and log output format. The tests use a similar pattern to `cmd/entire/cli/logging/logger_test.go` — writing to a buffer via the logging package then parsing JSON.\\n\\n```go\\npackage perf\\n\\nimport (\\n\\t\\\"context\\\"\\n\\t\\\"testing\\\"\\n\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n)\\n\\nfunc TestStart_CreatesRootSpan(t *testing.T) {\\n\\tt.Parallel()\\n\\tctx := context.Background()\\n\\n\\tctx, span := Start(ctx, \\\"test_op\\\")\\n\\tif span == nil {\\n\\t\\tt.Fatal(\\\"Start() returned nil span\\\")\\n\\t}\\n\\tif span.name != \\\"test_op\\\" {\\n\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"span.name = %q, want %q\\\", span.name, \\\"test_op\\\")\\n\\t}\\n\\tif span.parent != nil {\\n\\t\\tt.Error(\\\"root span should have nil parent\\\")\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\t// Verify span is in context\\n\\tgot := spanFromContext(ctx)\\n\\tif got != span {\\n\\t\\tt.Error(\\\"spanFromContext should return the span set by Start\\\")\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\tspan.End()\\n}\\n\\nfunc TestStart_NestsChildSpan(t *testing.T) {\\n\\tt.Parallel()\\n\\tctx := context.Background()\\n\\n\\tctx, parent := Start(ctx, \\\"parent\\\")\\n\\t_, child := Start(ctx, \\\"child\\\")\\n\\n\\tif child.parent != parent {\\n\\t\\tt.Error(\\\"child span should reference parent\\\")\\n\\t}\\n\\tif len(parent.children) != 1 {\\n\\t\\tt.Fatalf(\\\"parent should have 1 child, got %d\\\", len(parent.children))\\n\\t}\\n\\tif parent.children[0] != child {\\n\\t\\tt.Error(\\\"parent.children[0] should be the child span\\\")\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\tchild.End()\\n\\tparent.End()\\n}\\n\\nfunc TestEnd_RecordsDuration(t *testing.T) {\\n\\tt.Parallel()\\n\\tctx := context.Background()\\n\\n\\t_, span := Start(ctx, \\\"timed_op\\\")\\n\\ttime.Sleep(10 * time.Millisecond)\\n\\tspan.End()\\n\\n\\tif span.duration < 10*time.Millisecond {\\n\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"span.duration = %v, want >= 10ms\\\", span.duration)\\n\\t}\\n}\\n\\nfunc TestEnd_Idempotent(t *testing.T) {\\n\\tt.Parallel()\\n\\tctx := context.Background()\\n\\n\\t_, span := Start(ctx, \\\"double_end\\\")\\n\\ttime.Sleep(10 * time.Millisecond)\\n\\tspan.End()\\n\\n\\tfirstDuration := span.duration\\n\\n\\t// Second End should be a no-op\\n\\ttime.Sleep(10 * time.Millisecond)\\n\\tspan.End()\\n\\n\\tif span.duration != firstDuration {\\n\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"second End() changed duration from %v to %v\\\", firstDuration, span.duration)\\n\\t}\\n}\\n\\nfunc TestEnd_AutoEndsChildren(t *testing.T) {\\n\\tt.Parallel()\\n\\tctx := context.Background()\\n\\n\\tctx, parent := Start(ctx, \\\"parent\\\")\\n\\t_, child := Start(ctx, \\\"child\\\")\\n\\n\\t// Don't explicitly end child\\n\\ttime.Sleep(10 * time.Millisecond)\\n\\tparent.End()\\n\\n\\tif !child.ended {\\n\\t\\tt.Error(\\\"child should be auto-ended when parent ends\\\")\\n\\t}\\n\\tif child.duration == 0 {\\n\\t\\tt.Error(\\\"child should have non-zero duration after auto-end\\\")\\n\\t}\\n}\\n\\nfunc TestMeasure_TimesFunction(t *testing.T) {\\n\\tt.Parallel()\\n\\tctx := context.Background()\\n\\n\\t_, span := Start(ctx, \\\"parent\\\")\\n\\n\\tspan.Measure(\\\"substep\\\", func() {\\n\\t\\ttime.Sleep(10 * time.Millisecond)\\n\\t})\\n\\n\\tspan.End()\\n\\n\\tif len(span.children) != 1 {\\n\\t\\tt.Fatalf(\\\"expected 1 child from Measure, got %d\\\", len(span.children))\\n\\t}\\n\\tchild := span.children[0]\\n\\tif child.name != \\\"substep\\\" {\\n\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"child.name = %q, want %q\\\", child.name, \\\"substep\\\")\\n\\t}\\n\\tif child.duration < 10*time.Millisecond {\\n\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"child.duration = %v, want >= 10ms\\\", child.duration)\\n\\t}\\n}\\n\\nfunc TestSpanFromContext_ReturnsNilWhenEmpty(t *testing.T) {\\n\\tt.Parallel()\\n\\tctx := context.Background()\\n\\n\\tif got := spanFromContext(ctx); got != nil {\\n\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"spanFromContext on empty context = %v, want nil\\\", got)\\n\\t}\\n}\\n\\nfunc TestStart_MultipleChildren(t *testing.T) {\\n\\tt.Parallel()\\n\\tctx := context.Background()\\n\\n\\tctx, parent := Start(ctx, \\\"parent\\\")\\n\\n\\tctx2, child1 := Start(ctx, \\\"child1\\\")\\n\\t_ = ctx2\\n\\tchild1.End()\\n\\n\\tctx3, child2 := Start(ctx, \\\"child2\\\")\\n\\t_ = ctx3\\n\\tchild2.End()\\n\\n\\tparent.End()\\n\\n\\tif len(parent.children) != 2 {\\n\\t\\tt.Fatalf(\\\"expected 2 children, got %d\\\", len(parent.children))\\n\\t}\\n\\tif parent.children[0].name != \\\"child1\\\" {\\n\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"first child name = %q, want %q\\\", parent.children[0].name, \\\"child1\\\")\\n\\t}\\n\\tif parent.children[1].name != \\\"child2\\\" {\\n\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"second child name = %q, want %q\\\", parent.children[1].name, \\\"child2\\\")\\n\\t}\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Step 2: Run the tests**\\n\\nRun: `mise run test -- -run TestStart -v ./cmd/entire/cli/perf/`\\nExpected: All tests PASS\\n\\n**Step 3: Run fmt, lint, and full test suite**\\n\\nRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n\\n**Step 4: Commit**\\n\\n```bash\\ngit add cmd/entire/cli/perf/span_test.go\\ngit commit -m \\\"perf: add unit tests for span API\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Task 4: Instrument hook_registry.go — replace LogDuration with root span\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/commands/hook_registry.go` — the `newAgentHookVerbCmdWithLogging()` function\\n\\n**Step 1: Replace LogDuration with perf.Start/End**\\n\\nIn `newAgentHookVerbCmdWithLogging()`, find the existing timing code (around lines 109-161):\\n\\n```go\\n// Current code (approximate):\\nstart := time.Now()\\n// ... hook logic ...\\nlogging.LogDuration(ctx, slog.LevelDebug, \\\"hook completed\\\", start,\\n    slog.String(\\\"hook\\\", hookName),\\n    slog.String(\\\"hook_type\\\", hookType),\\n    slog.Bool(\\\"success\\\", hookErr == nil))\\n```\\n\\nReplace with:\\n\\n```go\\nctx, span := perf.Start(ctx, hookName,\\n    slog.String(\\\"hook_type\\\", hookType))\\ndefer span.End()\\n// ... rest of hook logic (remove old start/LogDuration) ...\\n```\\n\\nThe `span.End()` in defer will emit the root-level perf log with any child spans added downstream by lifecycle handlers and strategy methods.\\n\\n**Important:** Add the import `\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/perf\\\"` and remove unused `\\\"time\\\